XVth.C., on the left Death in centre walking Couple, a flute play right: Horst W. JANSON, 'A ""Memento mori"" among early Italian Prints', Warb.Journ. III, 1939/40, [3-4], pp. 243ff; c) Dürer, B. 94; d) Burgkmair, Clairobscur, Girl running away, death (with wings) [...] - Dürer: Wappen des Todes (B.10); Death as Dürer; Look up [James Midgley] Clark, Dance of Death [= The Dance of Death in the Middle Ages and the Renaissance, Glasgow: Jackson, 1950]; [Raimond] van Marle, Iconographie de l'art profane [au moyen-age et à la renaissance et la décoration des demeures, 2 vols., La Haye, Nijhoff, 1931-1932].",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
